reviews.review: Fan Service! A great, solid ending to the story I grew up with. Absolutely AWESOME movie!
I enjoyed this movie. I think many will not because it's a fantasy movie that wants you accept things without explanation. Just like we did with the OT. So don't over analyze it and enjoy the ride.

Now even though the movie isn't flawless or perfect, the critics honestly don't know what they are talking about when they call this film mediocre. But again this film wasn't made for them, it was made for the fans. "The Rise of Skywalker" displays the widest use of "the force" that has ever been seen in the films. It also has many heart touching and heart breaking moments that will have fans on a roller coaster of emotions.  Finally, the movie ends the Skywalker saga in a satisfying and memorable way.
It would have been better to have Abrams direct all 3. The lack of continuity is the biggest problem.

I read the leaks beforehand and the movie sounded like a disaster.  I went in not expecting much and left the theater very satisfied.  There are moments that truly capture Star Wars.  Rey is a fully fleshed out character in this film and she truly does have a powerful arc.  This is the same for Kylo Ren who in my opinion has been the strongest character in this series of films. 

Luke is handled well and I got to see the character I wanted since Return of the Jedi. 

Its a fun movie and a beautiful sendoff to these new characters while paying a beautiful homage to what has come before.  Do I see it as the end of the Skywalker Saga? No.  That ended with episode 6.  This is about the children of our heroes and their story and this film is wonderful conclusion.
was pretty good. but a good way to end it .

The movie plays with the emotions like no other. The ligthsaber fights are as amazing as the Space fights. The only Thing that annoys is that "The Rise of skywalker" makes "The Last Jedi" unnecessary.

Enjoyed it very much. It had a frenetic pace and deftly mined the previous films in the Skywalker Saga for inspiration and story telling. Particularly enjoyed finale, as it really hammered home the nature of family and how much it may mean. Solidly acted, deftly written and lushly orchestrated with intense special and practical effects melding seamlessly with the inspired acting of the protagonists.
A Star Wars movie that I will watch so many times. I loved it so much.
